content: Today I will introduce the game between I and Yamaguchi.
I wanted to become Meijin, so 1st game was so important.
As I was tentative black, I chose D11.
At Meijinsen tournament, I chose this 12
Probably you think it is advantages for black.
Yes, to tell the truth, I played this style against Mr. Nakamura 5years ago.
However, Yamaguchi was absent at that time.
I believed he did not know this variation deeply.
Of course he chose this 13th move.
He spent a little time so I thought he would change the move.
Because he is very fast player, do you know?
As I expected, he had changed the move at last.
I think, his purpose was black moves outside like this.
It might be possible, white is not so good, I guess.
This was had started 9:30, but until 21time was 12:00 already...
Did he spend lots of time on 21?
I had been thinking during lunch time.^^
Probably I spent 1hour more than he.
After the break, I made a decision.
how long do you have for each game?
GM,how long the 1st game last in all?
aurora is faster, as usual, how long a game takes?
Now both has 3:30 time in one game.
Several years ago, I had played till 22:00 against Nakamura.
what about the first meijin tournament?
Anyway, next move was so important.
But I believed he NEVER play at that point.
He spent lots of time and made a good move.
In this situation, white can not win from 26.
I was in trouble and a loss.
Do you prefer U or D?
I think i would play down
I think upper is safer. But Down is possible
The reason was right side is dangerous but not win for black.
I would have played if 27-J8  then 28-D6.
I dislike making four but he likes it..
In this situation, I must think the game balance.
For white, right-under side was most dangerous.
However, if black has no help, balck would not win.
So I would break the help for black from left side.
for me it seems as he missed his vct :)
yes, if black play here he can win
Yamaguchi said this 30 was the most unpleasant move..
If 30-I5, then black would play left side.
Are there any win for white?
G7 is the key point for black:)
As I thoght I could  defend, I chose safer.
Still, I was afraid right side
But his next move was for left side.
When I played 34, I thoght I would protect.
After that, Yamaguchi spent lots of time.
He said he was thinking how to move to get a draw.

35 was good for attacking but not good for protection.
If he wanted to get a draw, 35-E10 was better.
So white had to take care around 43.
44 was great help at the end of the game...
At 51th move, Yamaguchi proposed a draw.
if you cannot lose, do not accept the draw
However, at this move, both had a littel time remained.
So we did not think deeply from this.
Yamaguchi spent all time, his move must be whithin 1 min.
white seems strong in the upper right
IF I had played correctly, white could win easily.
Which stop, L, I or H 14?
L12 is very good and winning point.
In this time, black can make four!
Of course I was 1move 1 min situation...
As I was panic, I thought I never lost the game.
Next his move was the lost move.
When I made three, I found my victory.

The next day, 17th of Oct. 2nd game was held.
I think, D1 or I3 or D8 or....
8 would be usual move, I guess.
This pattern has many similar ones.
From I9, this 8th move is not good
But 9 is I7 better than I8
I was seeking some similar pattern.
I made a conclusion balck is not bad for this 8
It maybe only move for black.
Unexpectly, he played next move fast.
I thoght deeply and found the way.
If 13-I7 then black had to keep attacking.
I almost spent only my time.
His time was only whithin 20 min.
But I found the victory during lunch time.
To tell the truth, black could win from 25 directly.
I moved another attacking but no VCT.
Probably his 26 was the best protection.
I will introduce 3rd and 4th game, at the next lesson.
